headline: Paycom (PAYC): Buy, Sell, or Hold Post Q3 Earnings?
summary: Paycom has had an impressive run over the past six months as its shares have beaten the S&P 500 by 25%. The stock now trades at $230.17, marking a 38% gain. This was partly thanks to its solid quarterly results, and the performance may have investors wondering how to approach the situation.
